Jan Hrubý (born 3 December 1948, Prague, Czeschoslovakia) is a Czech rock violinist.
Between 1964-1968 he studied violin at the Prague Conservatory.
In 1984 he joined the Michael Prokop's Framus 5 and significantly influenced the album Kolej Yesterday.
